\section{Discrete Enumeration of the Local Neighborhood}
\label{sec:enumeration}

To provide additional descriptive context, we enumerate the value of $\chi^2 = ((Q_{\text{cell}} - Q_{\text{target}})/\sigma_Q)^2$ across a discrete grid in the (triple, target, scale, sign) space surrounding the observation. The grid contains $N = 10{,}640$ cells across five quark triples ($(u,d,s)$, $(s,c,b)$, $(c,b,t)$, $(u,c,t)$, $(d,s,b)$), thirty-eight rational target fractions $p/q$ with $q \leq 10$ in the physically relevant range, fourteen evaluation scales (all named particle masses through the Higgs plus several round-number reference scales), and four distinct sign assignments on the square roots after quotienting by global sign-flip invariance. The $\chi^2$ at each cell is computed using the propagated $\sigma_Q$ appropriate to that triple. Cells whose evaluation scale is below the perturbative regime for the relevant triple are flagged and excluded ($1{,}520$ cells); the remaining $9{,}120$ cells form the descriptive neighborhood.

\paragraph{What this enumeration is, and is not.} We emphasize at the outset that this enumeration is descriptive, not inferential. The $\chi^2$ values across cells are not draws from a stochastic null distribution; they are deterministic algebraic computations on the same fixed input masses, parameterized by the choice of (triple, target, scale, sign). Cells are not statistically independent: $Q(\text{triple})(\mu)$ is a smooth function of $\mu$, so neighboring (target, scale) cells within a triple are highly correlated. The $\sigma_Q$ used to define $\chi^2$ varies across triples by up to a factor of five (the FLAG uncertainties on the light quark masses are larger in fractional terms than the heavy quark masses), so the $\chi^2$ metric is not directly comparable across triples. We therefore do not interpret the rank of any cell within this enumeration as a $p$-value, percentile, or significance statement: it is a heuristic ordering that we use to characterize the local landscape, not a frequentist test result. With those caveats stated, the enumeration provides one further piece of context for the observation, which we report descriptively.

